args:
It turns out that the one behind everything was
Akasha, who had been working to awaken the
Nyarlathotep sleeping within Lathna. But after
Heinwald and Curran see through her plan,
the priestess acknowledges her failure.
This is where they took Lathna.
No need to be frightened, child.
I am indeed—and now we finally have a\nchance to speak, just the two of us.
What do you mean? Where's Curran\nand Heinwald?
In fact, I believe they are puttering around\nour church in a vain search for you.
For that is where I told them you would be.
Because I believed they would interfere\nwith you becoming your true self.
Surely you know to what I refer.\nSurely you understand the true you.
You are the emissary.\nThe silver key of His awakening.

I am... We... We are the emissary.
We are Chaos. Our body is the lock;
We are the key. A baleful path which
welcomes Him.
N Y A R L A T H O T E P
Heh heh! Yes, how simply wonderful.\nYou are Nyarlathotep. You are the key!
Now, let me embrace the key.
I am the gate; a gate of impurity, wrought\nto welcome Him. Wrench me open and\nawaken the Ancient One.
Our body is the key; wrought to extol\nthe Ancient One. And thus...
Gonna put the kibosh on that one, lady.
Hastur was never the gate.\nIt was you all along.
You insult me, priestess. Why would we\never believe she'd been taken to where\nHastur is? After all...
Hastur is not in this village at all.
All the Hasturs here are just transfigured\nvillagers. Copies, as it were. Correct?
Don't you remember what Hastur said\nwhen he gave the villagers his blessing?
＂Ensnarement of eternity. To you who\nhave passed long years, I recognize\nyour desire.＂
Long years? Now sure, it doesn't sound\nweird to say that to an old man...
But Hastur grants IMMORTALITY.\nWould he really refer to a few decades\nand change as ＂long years＂?
In other words, the Hastur who gave the\nblessing has the same perception of time\nthat we mortals do.
Meaning that Hastur, much like the\ntransformed villagers, was once a mortal\nperson just like any other.
Now, I cannot say with certainty where\nthe true Hastur is...
But I do not accept that you—a priestess of\nhis flock—were unaware that the one in\nyour village is a copy.

The only things in this village are pitiable
humans who received the blessing of a
false Hastur, and the priestess who has
been manipulating them this whole time!
Hey, when my man's right, he's right.\nTime to give it up, Akasha!
I do indeed appear to have underestimated\nyou. However, you are still a day late and\na copper short.
We are Chaos. A faceless emissary,\nbaying at moonlight. A key wrought\nin praise of the Ancient One.
Indeed, it is just as you say.
And how unfortunate that is for you.
We are the key; thus can we also lock.\nThat which opens. That which seals.\nThat which welcomes. That which rejects.
Our bonds are slack; and so the locking\nof the gate is mark of our freedom.
This cannot be! You are His EMISSARY!\nWould you truly not welcome Him?!
Our body is Chaos.\nThus is it free from burden.
You seem to be misunderstanding what\nNyarlathotep actually IS.

Our body is Chaos; thus is it free from
burden. We are the key by Our will.
Now will you gain reward for this plot
to ensnare Us!
I appear to have made a terrible,\nterrible mistake.
With things as they stand, it will be\nimpossible to open the gate.\nThus will I withdraw for now.

But! It is a long-established fact that the
Ancient One will descend upon our world.
Whether now, before, or in the future,
it is merely a question of when.
